# 3. Ansible Playbooks

A playbook is a YAML file that defines automation tasks.

## Example

```yaml
---
- name: Example Playbook
  hosts: all   # Run this playbook on all hosts from the inventory.
  become: yes  # Equivalent to running commands with sudo.

  tasks:
    - name: Install Apache
      yum:                 # Use the yum package manager
        name: httpd
        state: present      # Ensure it is installed (present)

    - name: Start Apache
      service:
        name: httpd
        state: started
```

## Key Components

| Field   | Description             |
| ------- | ----------------------- |
| hosts   | Target machines         |
| become  | Privilege escalation    |
| tasks   | Actions to execute      |
| modules | Tools like yum, service |

